<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-13T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-13T07:00:00-05:00" n="703" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d703">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/8–1345: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Pinkerton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Jerusalem</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-13T15:00:00+03:00">August 13,
                                    1945—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 7:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>146. My telegram 141, August 9, 11 a.m. Palestine Government has
                            authorized joining August and September quotas permitting entry <pb facs="0733" n="721" xml:id="pg_721"/> 3,000 in either month. Action
                            taken because shipping difficulties make arrival Mauritius refugees
                            during August doubtful. This makes provision for group referred to in
                            Department’s telegram 147 August 6<note n="13" xml:id="d703fn13">Not
                                printed.</note> and prevents charge of deliberate stretching of
                            White Paper quota if either month is filled.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Pinkerton</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>